snippet.title: Day 356 Beer Review: Independence Harbor Amber Ale, Rock Wall Brewing ALDI Beer HAPPY 4th of JULY!
snippet.description:
Day 356 of 365: Independence Harbor Amber Ale, Rock Wall Brewing (Genesee), Rochester, New York.
Purchased: ALDI, Findlay, Ohio
Brewery: https://www.geneseebeer.com

I picked up a six-pack of this patriotic themed amber ale at Aldi. This one comes in at 5.5% ABV and poured an amber color with moderate carbonation and an adequate white head. The nose was malty with a slight honey aroma. This was medium/light bodied and had a nice mouthfeel. You could pick up caramel malt, honey and that is about it. Overall, this was not a great beer, although it was not that bad either...I would try another, which is good, as I have 5 more in the six-pack!

#ABeerADayWithTK #BeerReview #IndependenceHarbor
